up issues**\\n\\nI think the failing Java run isn't due to dependencies or setup, but rather the tests being incompatible with the 3.3.5 API/JDK. I shouldn't decide on fixes just yet. It seems the current build has `--add-opens`, which raises questions about whether additional setup is required for tests using deep reflective private access. The user mentioned that the setup could involve environment properties or test code adjustments. I need to determine if this library needs anything beyond the normal generated scaffold for meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating JVM args for reflective access**\\n\\nI noticed that the existing tests had `jvmArgs --add-opens` because OGNL internals use reflective access to `java.lang` members. Now, I need to dig deeper into why `java.lang` requires the `add-opens` option. It might be necessary to search the source code for any private members in `java.lang` to understand this better. This exploration could help clarify whether the reflective access is truly essential for the tests to run smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Mm48vlkUJeV5Rss9wabgFiwT|fc_0e0cabfea811ec83016a3ef713721c8196b47cf719e95c01ce", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport zipfile, urllib.request, tempfile, pathlib, re\nurl='https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/ognl/ognl/3.3.5/ognl-3.3.5-sources.jar'\np=tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(delete=False,suffix='.jar').name\nurllib.request.urlretrieve(url,p)\nwith zipfile.ZipFile(p) as z:\n for name in z.namelist():\n  if name.endswith('.java'):\n   txt=z.read(name).decode('utf-8','replace')\n   if 'java.lang' in txt or 'setAccessible' in txt or 'add-opens' in txt or 'module' in txt:\n    lines=txt.splitlines()\n    for i,l in enumerate(lines,1):\n     if any(s in l for s in ['java.lang','setAccessible','AccessibleObject','getDeclaredField(\"override\"','ClassLoader']):\n      print(f'{name}:{i}:{l.strip()}')\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "op