[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java setup issues**\n\nI think the failing Java run isn't due to dependencies or setup, but rather the tests being incompatible with the 3.3.5 API/JDK. I shouldn't decide on fixes just yet. It seems the current build has `--add-opens`, which raises questions about whether additional setup is required for tests using deep reflective private access. The user mentioned that the setup could involve environment properties or test code adjustments. I need to determine if this library needs anything beyond the normal generated scaffold for meaningful coverage.\n\n**Investigating JVM args for reflective access**\n\nI noticed that the existing tests had `jvmArgs --add-opens` because OGNL internals use reflective access to `java.lang` members. Now, I need to dig deeper into why `java.lang` requires the `add-opens` option. It might be necessary to search the source code for any private members in `java.lang` to understand this better. This exploration could help clarify whether the reflective access is truly essential for the tests to run smoothly.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e0cabfea811ec83016a3ef70a93248196a2f300be0ce8aa94\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPvcTGGdbgf2tMz7NR16D8SZoSvvZ2wpvsM59JLIBkCKU1VaT9ZznIGlMkrry9Axixh7jFBKpX0pAUTNZoVbeVTkGKJYrxiLR1jaicYi-NWioRSsCXQTDa8HF5pjGE_mZpw-kQvcAhTUv4iKqUalqllZIQaJ0ycgRJMlVLNZ8VCuW4oGHzRDMH3JKiu_LN1hnPmpFYFFKmpKsQwjaFof9KDEE1LPpSFhJRcYYnUuaQwqp14s7V4XCfkRgRlRSDJZXkEMD_2Te9OCKoFJUWeG6m2kPNgfA4U_vQ6hucc510CKFCERoUTiTAwGsPxvgtRBp65AEcknwsjJwM2UaPm0ifF_Om_VYZzW5CQAWimNcJTFdfEa0e1i4Chd2yU9FYbUd07B-2qvPXPbLPX77jwT5KZVTI5FrTiQxBTG4vV4q_9YtP8v8ZlKKD7hXrAnFF6MVU57SqaMpGKev_KiEnB39OhBQN3kD4RzZ27WHpW-oYUZjsjOV4jUjZQ6LH5h-bwjDvcOjkQQUVHrBUyWxaNDMW0l6jroVLwCXlCjkOxen3ZKVZauF6KsZ5O0Kr5n75yU7pHj5_e6QxdZXHpD_fDBAmgmGsH7m1H_OgXN29bmd3AMYeYhFCmvqxjUtZ-LKMFIfzr8qW7iG2LmZeHA3GCvN1zXfmh